# Paperclip — Dispatch Cheatsheet (gitignored)

> Copy-paste commands to launch waves of your project. Keep this file open
> when running operations. Adjust placeholders to YOUR setup.
>
> Replace `<your-...>` placeholders before first use.

---

## Local setup (one time)

```bash
# ~/.config/<your-project>/paperclip.env (mode 600 on your machine)
PAPERCLIP_API_BASE=https://<your-tailscale-host>.tail<xxxx>.ts.net
PAPERCLIP_TOKEN=pcp_board_xxx   # cat /home/paperclip/.paperclip/auth.json on droplet

# Cached IDs (fill in after creating company + agents)
PROJECT_CO_ID=<co-id>
DEV_PRIMARY_1_ID=<id>
DEV_PRIMARY_2_ID=<id>
DEV_PRIMARY_3_ID=<id>
REVIEWER_ID=<id>
ROUTINE_REVIEW_PENDING_PRS_ID=<id>
```

```bash
# Source before each session
source ~/.config/<your-project>/paperclip.env
HEADERS=(-H "Authorization: Bearer $PAPERCLIP_TOKEN")
```

---

## Health snapshot (run before any wave)

```bash
# Agents — expect status: idle, lastHeartbeatAt < 30min if schedule on
curl -s "${HEADERS[@]}" \
  $PAPERCLIP_API_BASE/api/companies/$PROJECT_CO_ID/agents | \
  jq '.[] | {name, status, scheduleEnabled: .schedule.enabled, lastHeartbeatAt}'

# Open issues
curl -s "${HEADERS[@]}" \
  "$PAPERCLIP_API_BASE/api/companies/$PROJECT_CO_ID/issues?status=in_progress" | \
  jq '.[] | {id, title, assigneeAgentId}'

# Active routines
curl -s "${HEADERS[@]}" \
  $PAPERCLIP_API_BASE/api/companies/$PROJECT_CO_ID/routines | \
  jq '.[] | {id, title, status}'
```

