## Dispatch a wave (3 parallel tasks)

### 1. Create base branch `feat/<slug>`

```bash
cd <your-repo-path>
git fetch origin
git checkout -b feat/<your-feature-slug> origin/dev
git push -u origin feat/<your-feature-slug>
```

### 2. Create 3 issues (one per dev-primary)

```bash
# Reads issue bodies from local/paperclip/tasks/<feature-slug>/issues.md
# Each task block delimited by "## T<N> ..." header.
for n in 1 2 3; do
  TITLE=$(grep -m1 "^## T$n" local/paperclip/tasks/<your-feature-slug>/issues.md | sed "s/## //")
  BODY=$(awk "/^## T$n /,/^## T$((n+1)) |^---END---/" local/paperclip/tasks/<your-feature-slug>/issues.md | head -n -1)
  AGENT_VAR="DEV_PRIMARY_${n}_ID"

  curl -X POST "${HEADERS[@]}" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d "$(jq -n \
      --arg title "$TITLE" \
      --arg desc "$BODY" \
      --arg agent "${!AGENT_VAR}" \
      '{title:$title, description:$desc, status:"in_progress", priority:"medium", assigneeAgentId:$agent}')" \
    $PAPERCLIP_API_BASE/api/companies/$PROJECT_CO_ID/issues
done
```

### 3. Activate schedule on the 3 dev-primary

```bash
for id in $DEV_PRIMARY_1_ID $DEV_PRIMARY_2_ID $DEV_PRIMARY_3_ID; do
  curl -X PATCH "${HEADERS[@]}" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d '{"schedule":{"enabled":true,"intervalSec":120}}' \
    $PAPERCLIP_API_BASE/api/agents/$id
done
```

### 4. Watch progress

```bash
# Every 5 min, see status
watch -n 300 "curl -s '${HEADERS[@]}' \
  '$PAPERCLIP_API_BASE/api/companies/$PROJECT_CO_ID/issues' | \
  jq '.[] | {id, title, status, assigneeAgentId}'"

# Or via GitHub
gh pr list --base 'feat/<your-feature-slug>' --json number,title,labels,statusCheckRollup
```

### 5. Pause post-wave

```bash
for id in $DEV_PRIMARY_1_ID $DEV_PRIMARY_2_ID $DEV_PRIMARY_3_ID; do
  curl -X PATCH "${HEADERS[@]}" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d '{"schedule":{"enabled":false}}' \
    $PAPERCLIP_API_BASE/api/agents/$id
done
```

### 6. Open `feat -> dev` PR locally

```bash
cd <your-repo-path>
git fetch origin
git checkout feat/<your-feature-slug>
git pull origin feat/<your-feature-slug>   # pull squash-merges from the 3 task PRs

gh pr create \
  --base dev \
  --head feat/<your-feature-slug> \
  --title "feat(<your-feature-slug>): wave 1 — <summary>" \
  --body "Wave 1 of Paperclip orchestrator. 3 parallel tasks auto-merged via gate B:
- task/<your-feature-slug>/T1-<slug-1> (#<task-pr-1>)
- task/<your-feature-slug>/T2-<slug-2> (#<task-pr-2>)
- task/<your-feature-slug>/T3-<slug-3> (#<task-pr-3>)

Details in docs/tasks/<your-feature-slug>/.

Pilot reviews this PR and merges when ready."
```

